tball-data.org v4 base URL, so martj42 must fetch via `pd.read_csv(url)`. Use a cache-first design (read local cache file if present, else download and write cache) so tests and no-key runs stay fully offline and deterministic.\n\nConventions: module `\"\"\"docstring\"\"\"` \u2192 `from __future__ import annotations` \u2192 `logger`; pair the loader class with thin module-level `load_martj42_*` factory functions (mirrors `build_*_csv` / `generate_bracket_toml`). Pydantic config models use `ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")` and compose onto `AppConfig` in `config.py`.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `Martj42Loader.load_results()` returns a DataFrame with exactly `DATE, HOME_TEAM, AWAY_TEAM, HOME_GOALS, AWAY_GOALS, TOURNAMENT, NEUTRAL`; `\"NA\"` scores become `<NA>` in `Int64` columns; `\"TRUE\"`/`\"FALSE\"` become real `bool`\n- [ ] `load_shootouts()` and `load_goalscorers()` return their contract schemas (`WINNER/FIRST_SHOOTER`; `TEAM/SCORER/MINUTE/OWN_GOAL/PENALTY`)\n- [ ] Team-name columns (`HOME_TEAM`, `AWAY_TEAM`, and `TEAM` for goalscorers) pass through `normalize_team`/`normalize_series` from the crosswalk\n- [ ] New `REQUIRED_MARTJ42_*_COLUMNS` dicts + `validate_results_df`/`validate_shootouts_df`/`validate_goalscorers_df` wrappers; the martj42 validator accepts `Int64` and `bool` and raises `ValueError` (same \"missing column\"/\"wrong dtype\" contract as `loader.py`) on bad frames\n- [ ] Cache-first: no network read when the cache file exists; `Martj42Config` added to `config.py` and composed onto `AppConfig`; `dataset/martj42/*.csv` added to `.gitignore`\n- [ ] A `wc2026_schedule()` convenience filter returns `tournament == \"FIFA World Cup\"` rows including unplayed (`<NA>`-score) fixtures\n- [ ] Schema-verification tests assert the exact data-contract dtypes/columns; network is mocked (fixture CSV in `tmp_path` as cache, or patch `pd.read_csv`) \u201